<item>
            <title>[PIG-3307] Refactor physical operators to remove methods parameters that are always null</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3307</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The physical operators are sometimes overly complex. I&apos;m trying to cleanup some unnecessary code.&lt;br/&gt;
in particular there is an array of getNext(&lt;b&gt;T&lt;/b&gt; v) where the value v does not seem to have any importance and is just used to pick the correct method.&lt;br/&gt;
I have started a refactoring for a more readable getNext*T*().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
