                            <comment id="13646966" author="julienledem" created="Wed, 1 May 2013 22:32:13 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3307&quot; title=&quot;Refactor physical operators to remove methods parameters that are always null&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3307&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3307&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;_0.patch contains the initial refactoring&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13647171" author="julienledem" created="Thu, 2 May 2013 02:36:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3307&quot; title=&quot;Refactor physical operators to remove methods parameters that are always null&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3307&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3307&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;_1.patch introduces some more refactoring&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13647174" author="julienledem" created="Thu, 2 May 2013 02:38:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like we can get rid of the parameter that is only used for method dispatch.&lt;br/&gt;
I will replace all calls to getNext(Tuple t) to getNextTuple() in PhysicalOperator.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13648594" author="daijy" created="Fri, 3 May 2013 18:23:12 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Any performance implication for this change?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13648614" author="julienledem" created="Fri, 3 May 2013 18:47:55 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3307&quot; title=&quot;Refactor physical operators to remove methods parameters that are always null&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3307&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3307&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;_2.patch removes the unused parameter in getNext(&amp;#42;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13650021" author="julienledem" created="Mon, 6 May 2013 20:26:09 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daijy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daijy&quot;&gt;Daniel Dai&lt;/a&gt; This is removing parameters that were not used. I have not tested performance but I think it could only improve performance.&lt;br/&gt;
(see latest patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3307&quot; title=&quot;Refactor physical operators to remove methods parameters that are always null&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3307&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3307&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;_2.patch)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13650111" author="daijy" created="Mon, 6 May 2013 22:06:59 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s what I am expecting. Would love to see some performance data with this approach.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13651101" author="julienledem" created="Tue, 7 May 2013 18:46:15 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daijy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daijy&quot;&gt;Daniel Dai&lt;/a&gt;what&apos;s the recommended approach? If you have a setup to do perf test that would be helpful.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13654887" author="julienledem" created="Fri, 10 May 2013 22:46:07 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daijy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daijy&quot;&gt;Daniel Dai&lt;/a&gt; Also most likely it wont make any difference performance wise.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13657908" author="julienledem" created="Wed, 15 May 2013 05:56:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;It would be nice if someone could take a look before too many changes get in.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13658437" author="cheolsoo" created="Wed, 15 May 2013 16:14:06 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Do you mind uploading the patch to the RB?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will also run the unit tests with your patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13660033" author="julienledem" created="Thu, 16 May 2013 22:39:29 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/11203/diff/#index_header&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/11203/diff/#index_header&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
